This program demonstrates how to create and display custom characters on a 16Ã—2 LCD by using the CGRAM (Character Generator RAM) .
CGRAM allows defining up to 8 custom characters (locations 0â€“7), each with an 8-byte pixel pattern.

ğŸ”§ Key Functions

lcd_init()
